FBIS4-49924 "drchi092_k_94009" FBIS-CHI-94-092 Daily Report 12 May 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social `Religious' Activist Zhang Ruiyu Released on Parole `Religious' Activist Zhang Ruiyu Released on Parole OW1205031194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0305 GMT 12 May 94 OW1205031194 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, May 12 (XINHUA) -- Zhang Ruiyu, who was convicted in August 1990 of having conspired to overthrow the government by means of religious activities, has been released on parole, sources said here today. Zhang was sentenced to a term of imprisonment by the Putian city Intermediate People's Court of Fujian Province. The court recently ruled according to law that as she had abided by prison regulations and had behaved well during her imprisonment, she was qualified for release on parole.
